### Form-class protection (per-form, deliberately)
The slice-3 bug was: resolver used the strict API body schema, FormValues had
extra/blank-input keys it rejected, errors landed in `path: []` with no UI.
For cp3's five new forms:
- **Local resolver schema matching FormValues exactly** on all five —
  `inviteFormSchema` (3 strings), `teacherProfileFormSchema` (4 strings),
  `selfProfileFormSchema` (2 strings). None reuse the strict API body schema.
  Optional fields are plain `z.string().max()` (allow ""), so blank inputs
  never trip `.min(1).optional()` (the deferred.md empty-optional bug), and
  "" → null coercion happens on submit.
- **Root error block AND per-field errors render on every form.** Unexpected
  API errors go to `formState.errors.root`; field-specific ones
  (STAFF_NUMBER_TAKEN, EMAIL_TAKEN, INVITATION_ALREADY_PENDING) bind to the
  field via `setError`. No silent no-op submit anywhere.
- **ZERO `as never` casts.** Because each resolver's output type === its
  FormValues, the cast the deferred.md audit flags on the five academic
  dialogs was avoided from the start. cp3 adds none.

### Divergences from the cp3 prompt (all web-only-forced; documented)
- **`/staff/invite` is admin-only, not teacher-preselected.** `POST
  /users/invite` hardcodes `roleKey: "admin"` (inviteAdminSchema has no
  roleKey). Sending a "teacher" single-invite would silently grant ADMIN —
  privilege escalation — so there's no role dropdown; the form invites an
  admin and routes teacher invites to `/staff/import`. deferred.md +
  phase-1.md:1010 reconciliation added.
- **`/teacher/profile` nutNumber is read-only** (prompt said editable). The
  cp1 `/me` API (`updateMyTeacherProfileSchema.strict()`) accepts ONLY
  specialty + qualifications; a teacher sending nutNumber gets a 400. This
  matches phase-1.md:1022, which already specifies nutNumber read-only — so
  the SPEC agrees; only the prompt phrasing diverged.
- **`/staff` has no cursor pagination** — GET /users / GET /users/invitations
  return the full set; the teacher-profiles has-profile lookup pulls one
  page (limit 200) and surfaces an amber note if truncated. Fine at pilot
  scale; deferred.md entry added.
- **`/staff/[userId]` shows class-teacher arms but not assigned subjects** —
  subjects need TeacherAssignment (slice 11).

